FBIS4-68045 "jptot019__l94010" JPRS-TOT-94-019-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 5 May 1994 LATIN AMERICA HAITI Celeste FM Radio Owner Bastien Assassinated 4 May Celeste FM Radio Owner Bastien Assassinated 4 May FL0505194994 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1030 GMT 5 May 94 FL0505194994 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio French BFN [Text] We have learned from a reliable source that Jean-Verdy Bastien, owner of the Celeste Borlette Banks [lottery ticket offices] and of the private radio station, Celeste FM, was assassinated on the night of 4 May at about 2200 in upper Delmas. His driver was also injured during the attack against him by a group of armed men who had set up an ambush. According to our source, Jean-Verdy Bastien's body was transported to the general hospital morgue.
